# Deterministic Kernel Runtime with Canonical Storage Binding
## Example 10 — Formal Implementation Layer

---

## 1. Objective

This module implements a deterministic execution kernel whose state transitions produce verifiable outputs that are persistently stored using a canonical storage system defined by:

R = f(C, T, S)

Where:
- C = Configuration
- T = Storage Type (centralized | decentralized)
- S = Subtype (ipfs | node | postgresql)

The kernel does NOT assume storage semantics.
It only emits canonical state outputs.

